CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 18, 1970, pg. 18 reads: "Presenting Plaque - Three representatives of the George W. Gaines Lodge 144, F & A.M. of Philadelphia, presented a plaque in memory of Past Grand Master George W. Gaines to his window during the recent Grand Lodge Session of Masons at Hotel Webster Hall in Pittsburgh. The plaque was for "the many years of outstanding service to the community" through the funeral home the late Mr. Gaines headed.  Left to right: Worshipful Master Nathaniel Caldwell (Making presentation), Emery Swints, Mrs. Julia Gaines McGarrity, and Calvin M. Davenger, Mrs. McGarrity is carrying on the business founded by her late husband. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Plaque presented to Gaines Funeral Parlor in memory of George W. Gaines, Webster Hall
